Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, with gradual curve. Clay near fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0337.21. Pencil '37'?'. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0457)
